<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Beweep" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Beweep,</orth> 1) to weep over: <bibl n="shak. son 29.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 29, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.328" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 328</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.251" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 251</bibl> (Ff. <emph>he bewept my fortune;</emph> Qq <emph>when I parted with him</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.324" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 324</bibl>.<lb />2) to bedew with tears: <cit><quote>sweet flowers, which bewept to the grave did go with true-love showers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 38</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>